Describe another city you would like to stay for a short time
- what it is
- what it offers
- when you went there
- explain why you would like to stay there for a short time

I’d like to talk about Vung Tau, a coastal city in the south of Vietnam, which I would love to stay in for a short time. It’s well known for its beautiful beaches, scenic mountains, and fresh seafood, making it a popular destination for weekend getaways.

I’ve actually been there a few times, and the last time was about two years ago, when I was a second-year university student. After finishing my final exams, I went on a short trip with some close friends to relax. We stayed there for three days and had an amazing time exploring different attractions, trying local dishes, and visiting cozy seaside cafés.

There are several reasons why I’d like to go back for another short stay. Firstly, I’ve been quite stressed lately, so I think spending a few days there would help me unwind and recharge. As someone who loves the beach, I really enjoy lying on the sand and listening to the sound of the waves, which I find incredibly relaxing.

Another reason is that Vung Tau is quite close to where I live, only about a two-hour drive, so it’s very convenient for a short trip without spending too much time traveling. Overall, it’s one of my favorite destinations, and I’d love to revisit it to relive those great memories and take a break from my daily routine.
